# Copy to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) for local `wrangler dev`. Literal values only. Never commit the
# filled-in copy.
#
# THIS FILE IS ALSO THE "Deploy to Cloudflare" PROMPT LIST: Cloudflare reads it and asks for each key
# on the setup form. So it is kept SHORT ON PURPOSE — only what a first deploy actually needs. Every
# key added here becomes one more blank box a newcomer has to understand.
#
# Everything else is optional and documented in SETUP.md. Add it later with:
#     wrangler secret put <NAME>          # secrets
#     ...or edit `vars` in wrangler.jsonc # non-secret config
#
# NS_SERVER and NS_PORTAL_ISS are NOT here: they live in wrangler.jsonc `vars` and are prompted from
# there. A key in both places is prompted twice and then shadowed by the config value at runtime —
# silently ignoring whatever was typed.

# ── The one secret a normal deploy needs. ──
# A NetSapiens API token. Reads run as this token, so its NetSapiens scope is the real boundary — a
# reseller-scoped token can read every domain it covers. Prefer the narrowest token that works.
#
# LEAVE BLANK if you are running portal mode (PORTAL_MODE=1), where each request carries the calling
# user's own ns_t and no stored token exists at all. See SETUP.md.
NS_API_TOKEN=""

# ── Optional: who sees which portal features. ──
# Portal-mode features (call-flow, app columns, banner) are gated to roles by DEFAULT — you need nothing
# here to get the defaults. To hide/re-level a feature or add a superadmin, set PORTAL_FEATURES (JSON) /
# PORTAL_SUPERADMINS. Full level vocabulary, registry, and examples: SETUP.md → "Features & gating".
